## What the tests cover

| Area | Test class | Key assertions |
|---|---|---|
| **Authentication** | `TestAuthentication` | Unauthenticated users raise `AuthenticationError`; no DB or audit side-effects |
| **Authorisation** | `TestAuthorisation` | Non-manager roles raise `PermissionError`; no DB or audit side-effects |
| **Field validation** | `TestMandatoryFieldValidation` | Each mandatory field (`name`, `code`) individually missing/blank; format constraints on `code`; length constraint on `name`; all errors returned at once; no DB or audit side-effects on failure |
| **Successful creation** | `TestSuccessfulCreation` | Department persisted with correct payload; optional fields handled; minimal (mandatory-only) form accepted |
| **Audit record** | `TestAuditRecord` | Audit called once; correct entity, action, entity ID, and user recorded; ordering (persist → audit); no audit on DB failure |
| **Edge cases** | `TestIdempotencyAndEdgeCases` | Boundary-value name length; valid code formats; multiple creations produce independent audit entries; return value is the persisted object |
